  "comments": "<p>Banknote in UV light<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6105243e63066.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6105243e63066.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a><br>The back contains UV<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6526a980d6cd7.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6526a980d6cd7.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a><br>© ByRussia45<br>The banknote contains a security strip with the inscription \"1 ГРН\" with the national emblem and a see-through register<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6526a9c840444.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6526a9c840444.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a><br>© ByRussia45<br>V.S. Stekmakh was Chairman of the Central Bank of Ukraine from 2000 until 2002 and from 2004 until 2010<br>S.H. Arbuzov was Chairman of the Central Bank of Ukraine from 2010 until 2012<br>V.O. Hontareva was Chairman of the Central Bank of Ukraine from 2014 until May 11, 2017<br>I.V. Smoliy was Chairman of the Central Bank of Ukraine from 2018 until July 3, 2020</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6959755d600d8.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6959755d600d8.jpg\"></a><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/695975674cea8.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/695975674cea8.jpg\"></a></p>",
